'''Roy William Stroud''' (15 March 1925 – 4 June 2015) was an English professional [[Association football|football]] [[inside right]] who played as an [[outside right]] for [[Hendon F.C.|Hendon]], [[West Ham United F.C.|West Ham United]] and [[Chelmsford City F.C.|Chelmsford City]].<ref name="whustats">{{cite web | url=http://www.westhamstats.info/westham.php?west=2&ham=622&united=Roy_Stroud| title=Welcome to the Wonderful World of West Ham United Statistics&nbsp;— Roy Stroud | publisher=www.westhamstats.info | accessdate=17 April 2014}}</ref> He was capped by [[England national amateur football team|England]] at amateur level.<ref name="Hugman">{{cite web | accessdate=2016-10-26 | url=http://hugmansfootballers.com/player/18992 | title=Barry Hugman's Footballers - Roy Stroud | website=hugmansfootballers.com}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.englandfootballonline.com/MatchRsl/MatchRslAm2.html|title=England Matches - The Amateurs 1947-1962|website=www.englandfootballonline.com|accessdate=2016-10-26}}</ref>

==Footballing career==
Born in [[Silvertown]], London, his parents moved to [[Hounslow]] when he was young. Stroud started playing with London and Middlesex boys before being selected for England boys as an outside right. During the [[World War II|Second World War]] he was a guest player for [[Arsenal F.C.|Arsenal]] and [[Brentford F.C.|Brentford]].<ref>{{cite book | title=Who's Who of West Ham United | publisher=Independent Uk Sports Publications | author=Hogg, Tony | year=1995 | location=London | pages=197 | isbn=1-899429-01-8}}</ref> Stroud then played for Hendon before moving to West Ham in February 1952 and making his debut against [[Notts County F.C.|Notts County]] on 14 April 1952. It was his only [[Football League|league]] appearance that season. He would have to wait over 18 months for his next appearance. In this game, on 7 November 1953, Stroud scored his first goal for West Ham in a 5–0 home win against [[Bury F.C.|Bury]]<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.11v11.com/matches/west-ham-united-v-bury-07-november-1953-107083/| title=West Ham United v Bury, 7 November 1953 | publisher=www.11v11.com | accessdate=26 April 2014}}</ref> He also scored in his next game, on 14 November 1953, a 3–1 away defeat by [[Oldham Athletic F.C.|Oldham Athletic]]. His run of games amounted to only four that season, one in [[1954–55 Football League|1954–55]], two in [[1955–56 Football League|1955–56]] and five in his final season, [[1956–57 Football League|1956–57]].<ref name=whustats/> He played only 15 times in his West Ham career in all competitions, scoring four goals before signing for [[Chelmsford City F.C.|Chelmsford City]] in 1957.

==Death==

Stroud died on 4 June 2015 in [[Devon]] at age 90, having been suffering with [[dementia]].<ref name=":0" /> He was the oldest surviving West Ham United player at the time of his death.<ref name=":0">{{cite web | url=http://www.whufc.com/News/Articles/2015/July/23-July/Roy-Stroud-1925-2015? | title=Roy Stround 1925-2015 | publisher=www.whufc.com | accessdate=26 July 2015}}</ref>

